Git for bash


Install and save this repo (for updates)

1) Get this                            : git clone git://github.com/progman/gitbash.git ~/.gitbash.git
2) Add this in your .bashrc line       : echo "source ~/.gitbash.git/.gitbash" >> ~/.bashrc
3) cd in your git repo


Install and kill this repo (for minimize size)

1) Get this                            : git clone git://github.com/progman/gitbash.git ~/.gitbash.git
2) Copy file .gitbash in your home dir : cp ~/.gitbash.git/.gitbash ~
3) Add this in your .bashrc line       : echo "source ~/.gitbash" >> ~/.bashrc
4) Kill this repo                      : rm -rf ~/.gitbash.git
5) cd in your git repo
